activities.message:
This is indeed a genuine and security related problem exactly as reported and described by @nyymi . This has existed since libcurl 7.61.0 with the commit linked above. CVSS is tricky for this, but I think "Low" still seems fair. Feel free to tell me how I'm wrong on this.

I have an initial proposed patch attached, but I haven't actually test-built it on Windows so could be fatally flawed.

@nyymi: I would like to work on this fix and corresponding advisory and announce it in sync with the planned next curl release (7.77.0) on May 26. You okay with this?
